title.narrative: Increased capacity of right-holders and duty bearers to foster positive practices and norms to protect children from violence,abuse, exploitation and neglect

description.narrative: In 2021, efforts applied a greater intergenerational and gender-responsive approach in addressing violence and its disproportional impact on women and girls. Interventions increased the capacities of over 3000 teachers, 45 civil society organizations, 24 faith-based organizations, 38 private sector organizations and community leaders, women, and children in 25 communities across Belize, on legislation, protection, and procedures for family violence issues. 138 government officials received capacity building and mentorship opportunities to improve their understanding, response, and support to children and families affected by violence. As a result, over 115,000 children and women will benefit from improved and enhanced services. | Status:Met | As-of Date:11/01/2022
